## 3. Solver log signature — cumulative targets visible

In R6c (Fix #14 only), partition 2's log showed:
```
Sample (resource=1): 2026-05=[rt=3/4, ct=1/2, comb=3/5, full_month=False]
```
Required=3 for partition 2 was correct cumulatively, but partition 3's `rt=0` (required=0) locked in the undercount.

In R7b (Fix #14 + #15), the same run emits:
```
[Partition 0]   Sample (resource=1): 2026-04=[rt=1/1], 2026-05=[rt=1/1]            (cum_day=3,  gross=1)
[Partition 1]   Sample (resource=1): 2026-04=[rt=0/1], 2026-05=[rt=3/4]            (cum_day=24, gross=4)
[Partition 2]   Sample (resource=1): 2026-05=[rt=0/4, full_month=False]            (cum_day=31, gross=4, prior_rt=4)
[Partition 3]   Sample (resource=1): 2026-05=[rt=0/4, full_month=False]            (cum_day=31, gross=4, prior_rt=4)
```
Each partition's gross climbs to the cumulative target by its seg_end. The last partition covering each month sees gross = full-month target. Prior allocations zero-out the required. Solver doesn't over-allocate (Fix #13 excess penalty holds). Every (resource, segment) lands at exactly the legal minimum or above.

