## 5. Files changed in Fix #15

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| `solver_v2/preprocessing/rest_targets.py` | `compute_rest_targets` now takes optional `full_plan_start, full_plan_end`. Proration formula changed from `days_in_segment / days_in_full_month` to `cumulative_days / days_in_full_month`, where `cumulative_days = seg_end.day - month_cum_start_day + 1`. `is_full_month` flag redefined against full plan range. |
| `solver_v2/solver/partitioner.py` | `Partition.full_plan_start` + `Partition.full_plan_end` fields added. `create_partitions` populates from `min_date`, `max_date`. `solve_partition` stashes on preprocessed. |
| `solver_v2/solver/checkpoint_manager.py` | `_split_oversized_partition` forwards both fields to sub-partitions (same pattern as Fix #14). |
| `solver_v2/solver/model.py` | LC-06 block reads `getattr(self.data, 'full_plan_start', None) or planning_start_date` and passes as `full_plan_start` kwarg to `compute_rest_targets`. Same for `end`. |

**Zero other file changes.** No analyzer modifications needed (they use the default fallback path). No config flag needed (the fix is always-on; if `full_plan_start` is None, falls back to pre-Fix-#15 math).

